<paragraph id="8BC336E9D2029D2F3AD4DBF5EC6BFD19" blockId="23.[136,799,681,775]" box="[136,539,717,739]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D6AD2029D2F3AD4DBF5EF4DFD18" authorityName="Garbini" authorityYear="1902" box="[136,317,717,738]" class="Dinophyceae" family="Peridiniaceae" genus="Peridinium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peridiniales" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" phylum="Myzozoa" rank="species" species="alatum">
<emphasis id="B908EAFBD2029D2F3AD4DBF5EF4DFD18" box="[136,317,717,738]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Peridinium alatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Garbini (1902: 122)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336E9D2029D2F3AD4DBC9ED6FFCFD" blockId="23.[136,799,681,775]" box="[136,799,753,775]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D6AD2029D2F3AD4DBC9EFAFFCFC" box="[136,479,753,774]" class="Dinophyceae" family="Peridiniaceae" genus="Peridinium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peridiniales" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" phylum="Myzozoa" rank="variety" species="willei" variety="carinthiacum">
<emphasis id="B908EAFBD2029D2F3AD4DBC9EF5FFCFC" box="[136,303,753,774]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Peridinium willei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B908EAFBD2029D2F3B03DBC9EFAFFCFC" box="[351,479,753,774]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">carinthiacum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Beck-Mannagetta (1931: 229)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336E9D2029D2F3AD4DA0DEC15FCAA" blockId="23.[136,1452,821,1928]" box="[136,613,821,848]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Dimensions: L: 49–74 µm, Td: 32–67 µm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336E9D2029D2F3AE1DA61EC83FC62" blockId="23.[136,1452,821,1928]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">
Cell shape: Highly variable, from sub-spherical to deflated ball shape, that is, with a strong sinking in the ventral part of the epitheca as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D6AD2029D2F3BFDDA46ECF3FC6D" box="[417,643,893,919]" class="Dinophyceae" family="Peridiniaceae" form="lineatum" genus="Peridinium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peridiniales" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" phylum="Myzozoa" rank="form" species="willeli">
<emphasis id="B908EAFBD2029D2F3BFDDA46EC73FC6D" box="[417,515,893,919]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">P. willeli</emphasis>
f. 
<emphasis id="B908EAFBD2029D2F387DDA45ECF3FC6D" box="[545,643,893,919]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">lineatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F38CFDA45EC96FC62" box="[659,742,893,920]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336E9D2029D2F3AE1DA99EC39FBD2" blockId="23.[136,1452,821,1928]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">
Thecal characteristics: Tabulation, 4ʹ, 3a, 7ʹʹ, 5C, 6S, 5ʹʹʹ, 2ʹʹʹʹ. Without apical pore. In the spherical specimens, the plates are more uniform in the term of development of their axis. Plate 1ʹ very variable, from an almost rhombic shape (
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F3ACCDAD1EE84FBFE" box="[144,244,1001,1028]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Fig. 16B</figureCitation>
) to fan-shaped (
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F3BF0DAD1EC63FBFE" box="[428,531,1001,1028]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Fig. 16C</figureCitation>
). Plate 2a is of hexa symmetrical 
<typeStatus id="54C7884BD2029D2F39D3DAD2EDCFFBFE" box="[911,959,1002,1028]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">type</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F3993DAD1EAD7FBFE" box="[975,1191,1001,1028]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Figs. 16D and 16E</figureCitation>
). The adcingular plates 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D6AD2029D2F3AD4DD35EF51FBDD" box="[136,289,1037,1063]" form="cingular" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" rank="form">form cingular</taxonomicName>
lists typical for the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336E9D2029D2F3AE1DD09ED1AFB95" blockId="23.[136,1452,821,1928]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Cingulum and sulcus: Descendent cingulum. The sulcus penetrates slightly into the epitheca and reaches the antapex, being narrower in the anterior part and wider posteriorly.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336E9D2029D2F3AE1DD41ECAFFB4D" blockId="23.[136,1452,821,1928]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">
Ecdysial opening: As in most of the species of the genus (
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B18D2029D2F3933DD41EA34FB6E" author="Boltovskoy, A." box="[879,1092,1145,1172]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" pagination="331 - 344" refId="ref13578" refString="Boltovskoy, A. (1973 b) Peridinium gatunense Nygaard. Estructura y estereoultraestructura tecal (Dinoflagellida). Physis (Buenos Aires) B 32: 331 - 344." type="journal article" year="1973">Boltovskoy 1973b</bibRefCitation>
) the opening is a result of the detachment of the seven dorsal plates of the epitheca.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336E9D2029D2F3AE1DDF9EF23FA6A" blockId="23.[136,1452,821,1928]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">
Ornamentation: The main thecal plates have a relief reticulum formed by solid cords and nodules, with pores inside the alveolus. Tabular margins bordered by slightly prominent marginal ridges. A remarkable difference with the other species of the genus, except with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D6AD2029D2F381CDC32ECB5FAD9" authorityName="Lemmermann" authorityYear="1900" baseAuthorityName="Hedger et al." baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[576,709,1289,1315]" class="Dinophyceae" family="Peridiniaceae" genus="Peridinium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peridiniales" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" phylum="Myzozoa" rank="species" species="limbatum">
<emphasis id="B908EAFBD2029D2F381CDC32ECB5FAD9" box="[576,709,1289,1315]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">P. limbatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is the development of three hyaline lists arisen from the marginal ridges of the anterior edges of the plates 2ʹ+4ʹ, 1a+3ʹ+3a and 2a. (
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F3907DC15EDD9FAB2" box="[859,937,1325,1352]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
C-F). These lists are continuous strips situated perpendicularly to the sagittal plane. At the antapex there are also lists, located on eiher side of the posterior end of the sulcus (
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F3A81DC4DEF36FA6A" box="[221,326,1397,1424]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Fig. 16G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336E9D2029D2F3AE1DCA1EF9EFA2D" blockId="23.[136,1452,821,1928]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">
Localities: Riogrande II reservoir in North-west, De La Regadera reservoir, Chisacá, La Cristalina, Media, and El Pozo lakes in central 
<collectingCountry id="F36B7679D2029D2F3B24DC85EF9AFA2D" box="[376,490,1469,1495]" name="Colombia" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336E9D2029D2F3AE1DCD9EEA1F8E1" blockId="23.[136,1452,821,1928]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">
Commentaries: Two forms of this species were found in the analyzed samples, the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D6AD2029D2F3ED3DCD9EABDFA01" authorityName="Huitfeldt-Kaas" authorityYear="1900" box="[1167,1229,1505,1531]" class="Dinophyceae" family="Peridiniaceae" genus="Peridinium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peridiniales" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" phylum="Myzozoa" rank="species" species="willei">
<emphasis id="B908EAFBD2029D2F3ED3DCD9EABDFA01" box="[1167,1229,1505,1531]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">willei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D6AD2029D2F3E84DCD9EB3BFA01" box="[1240,1355,1505,1531]" form="with" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" rank="form">form with</taxonomicName>
1ʹ plate expands laterally in an extraordinary way (
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F3835DF3DECBDF9DA" box="[617,717,1541,1568]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Fig. 16C</figureCitation>
) and the lateral epithecal plates and especially those of the apical region are tapered, forming two strips that run the epitheca from side to side (
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F39B9DF11EAC6F9BE" box="[997,1206,1577,1604]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Figs. 16E and 16F</figureCitation>
). In this case, 1ʹʹ plate is three times shorter than 7ʹʹ plate (
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F3841DF75ECF2F992" box="[541,642,1613,1640]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Fig. 16C</figureCitation>
) and cingular lists are more prominent. These specimens were found in Chisacá and El Pozo (lakes) and were larger than those of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B18D2029D2F3976DF49EA7EF971" author="Boltovskoy, A." box="[810,1038,1649,1675]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" refId="ref13675" refString="Boltovskoy, A. (1999 a) Contribucion al conocimiento de los dinoflagelados de la Republica Argentina. Universidad de La Plata. 148 pp." type="book" year="1999">Boltovskoy (1999a)</bibRefCitation>
. The 
<emphasis id="B908EAFBD2029D2F3E13DF49EAC1F971" box="[1103,1201,1649,1675]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">lineatum</emphasis>
form (
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F3F5DDF49EB19F976" box="[1281,1385,1649,1676]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
) with 1ʹ plate rhombic shape (
<figureCitation id="13472A6CD2029D2F3BC5DFADEC70F94A" box="[409,512,1685,1712]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,191,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-19@24.[151,1436,190,1887]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 16. Peridinium willei f. willei: A. Ventral view. B. Plate 1’. Bar=10µm. P. willei f. lineatum: C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Dorsal apical view. F. Lateral view. G. Antapical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426119/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Fig. 16B</figureCitation>
), these were found in Riogrande II and De La Regadera (reservoirs), La Cristalina and Media (lakes), was in the range of the measures cited by the same author (
<tableCitation id="C6FE0352D2029D2F39ABDF81EA3DF929" box="[1015,1101,1721,1747]" captionStart="TABLE 9" captionStartId="25.[136,224,159,183]" captionText="TABLE 9. Variation of length (L) and trans-diameter (Td) of Peridinium willei in Colombia. (n=10 in each locality)" pageId="23" pageNumber="158">Table 9</tableCitation>
) and larger than those reported in previous taxonomic studies (
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B18D2029D2F3BAEDFE5EC88F90D" author="Hansen, G. &amp; Flaim, G." box="[498,760,1757,1783]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" pagination="107 - 141" refId="ref15090" refString="Hansen, G. &amp; Flaim, G. (2007) Dinoflagellates of the Trentino Province, Italy. Journal of Limnology 66: 107 - 141. https: // doi. org / 10.4081 / jlimnol. 2007.107" type="journal article" year="2007">Hansen &amp; Flaim 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B18D2029D2F395BDFE5ED9AF90D" author="Huitfeld-Kaas, H." box="[775,1002,1757,1783]" pageId="23" pageNumber="158" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref15293" refString="Huitfeld-Kaas, H. (1900) Die limnetischen Peridineen in norwegischen Binnenseen. Videnskabsselskabets Skritter. I. Mathematisknaturvidenskabelig Klasse 2: 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1900">Huitfeld-Kaas 1900</bibRefCitation>
